hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I can't hear you very well jobs.coremedicalgroup.com The National Guardsmen politely refused my request for entry even before I had finished explaining I had permission, slapping down an orange traffic cone in front of my Jeep as if I might be tempted to run the checkpoint. I've covered many disasters and have come to understand that politeness, respect and understanding go a long way for anyone working or recovering. I pulled over and prepared to wrangle -- and that's when the state police corporal showed up. I never got his name, but he knew I had permission to pass through the roadblocks and offered to escort me through to Glen Haven because he was heading down there to drop off Red Cross supplies.
